        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=1735&FORUM_ID=6&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=The+Great+Necro+Talks+2002&Topic_Title=Necro+%22Balancing%22"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> I agree with Zarloth. Necros, IMHO, are an offensive class, and should be capable of dealing damage. I think the following changes need to be made to "balance" our class:</P><P>1. Pre-50 none.. except to change ignite bones to no skeleton illusion or make new non-illusion spell something that is aquireable by a 44 necro thru combat. An example of the chaos this has caused in the past is summon corpse.</P><P>2. Give us an alternate advancement skill that really increases the damage of DOT spell. The only offensive spells that have really been addressed in alternate advancement and new focus items are direct damage spells. Why are DOTS completely overlooked in regard to damage. One argument is that we can decrease the time/mana to cast these spells, but I am more concerned about damage output. One way to do this might be do give the necromancer a chance or the ability to decrease the duration of DOT spells while keeping damage output the same. Or have critical DOTS.. where the damage amount is increased.</P><P>3. In areas like the arena at kael MOBS fall down so fast that DOTs are pretty much useless. Give us a decent DD spell post 50. Something to where we are capable of making a difference.</P><P>4. What is wrong with FD? Post 50 I think the chance of FD failing should be VERY small. I haven't tested FD but I would be very curios to see what the failure rate is at lv 50. I would guess that it is as high as 30 percent.</P><P>In summary I would like to see the necromancer become more offensivley capable post 50. I am hoping that the post 50 necro does not continue to be used only to twitch group members in need of mana or a support class post 50, and given the choice of having a support role or an offensive damage dealing role post 50 I would choose to inflict damage and leave the support roles to the classes that do a far better job of fulfilling this role.</font></td>

