        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> We have discussed this till we are blue in the face.  Dot Stacking.</P><P>Verant thinks that necros will once again be too powerful with Dot Stacking, but they don't say jack about Quadkiting wizards, AE groups killing 60+ mobs with one mana bar, a 60 wizard with crits doing MASS dmg in short amount of time, but yet, Dot stacking will make us too powerful.</P><P>They say it is in the code to not allow dots to stack and it will take too mich to change it.  Let me ask you a question....how is it that HoT's (Heals over Time) can be stacked, Bond of Death and Vexing can stack, but regular dots cannot.  Hell we have dots that wont stack with enchanter spells and shaman dots.</P><P>This isn't a coding issue where it cannot be done, merely an issue where they don't want it done.  I can completely understand the not stacking of say darkness line, or cess line where it acts as a debuff or snare.  Makes sense to me.  But Pyro, Splurt, etc etc.  There is no added effect of snare, debuff, etc.  Just straight dmg over time.  This can easily be made to be stackable with some coding changes.</P><P>Seriously, it really is time for Verant to see the big picture here and make it worthwhile to play this class.</P><P></P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
