        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Where did VI say dot stacking would <i>never</i> be implemented?  Correct me if I'm wrong, but it was said that it would take time due to coding difficulties...</P><P>BTW, I think the primary issue Jahaar mentioned on these boards a while back was that a mob almost always loses track of who cast a spell when the spellcaster zones.  Hence, allowing dotstacking now == zone-in/zone-out exploiting...not to mention that they'll need to add a lot of extra buff slots to NPCs, and I would imagine there are other issues as well.</P><P>Just give it a rest on all the cynicism.  They *know* we want dot stacking, badly.  Give them some time, caster balancing isn't even over yet.</P><P>Aatudien, 59 necromancer of Lanys T'Vyl<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
